Health Minister Zweli Mkhize. eNCA/Heidi Giokos JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is expected to respond to allegations about irregular multi-million rand contracts by his department. Mkhize’s close associates are said to have benefited. The Daily Maverick reports that the department paid communications company Digital Vibes R150-million for services. READ: Phase 2 rollout: Mkhize allays COVID-19 vaccine fears It is alleged that the company received millions of rand for scheduling Mkhize’s media briefings on the ongoing coronavirus pandemic. Mkhize will provide an update on the investigation.